Thousands of migrants who illegally crossed the US’s southern border recently and claimed asylum are enjoying a slew of free perks in New York City. Mayor Eric Adams — warning that the Biden administration’s border policies could cost the city more than a mind-boggling $1 billion because of the influx — has begged the White House to help the Big Apple bear the burden, to no avail. Here are some of the benefits that come along with being an asylum-seeker in the Big Apple. Courtesy of the city: Courtesy of private groups: